cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses multithreaded execution of programs using Transactional Memory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a new concurrency control protocol. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of off-the-shelf HTM. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of Pot prototypes. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the performance evaluation of Pot.
